    "These neurons represent market actions (-1, 0, or 1) and the price prediction score (ranging from -100 to 100).",
    "The DQN model contains three fully connected dense layers, each containing 64 neurons.",
    "These layers aim to capture the complex relationships between the input features and actions.",
    "Increasing the number of neurons and layers allows the model to learn more complex patterns, at the expense of increased computational cost and risk of overfitting.",
    "Each dense layer utilizes a ReLU activation function to prevent vanishing gradient issues during training."
